Addendum: Engineering Findings (2025-10-07)

This section summarizes the current implementation as observed in the repository and highlights gaps from the prior PDF overview. It is additive and does not replace or remove the original content above.

System Overview
- Edge + Cloud: React frontends (POS and Admin) connect to a Rust microservice backend.
- Multi-tenant: All business data is tenant-scoped; requests include `X-Tenant-ID` and JWT claims enforce tenancy.
- Event-driven: Kafka decouples workflows (e.g., `order.completed`, `payment.completed`).
- Deployability: Docker Compose for dev; Terraform for AWS; Vault/Redis/Postgres/Kafka included.

Frontends
- POS Edge Client (`frontends/pos-app`)
  - Offline-first PWA using `vite-plugin-pwa` with Workbox caching.
  - Product catalog cached per-tenant in `localStorage`; offline order queue with idempotency keys.
  - Communicates with `order-service` and `integration-gateway` via REST; polls for status (WebSocket URL scaffolded but backend WS not implemented).
- Admin Portal (`frontends/admin-portal`)
  - React + Vite with simple RBAC (`rbac.ts`), pages for Products, Orders, Users, Settings, and Reporting.
  - Uses JWT from `auth-service` and `X-Tenant-ID` for admin operations.

Microservices (Rust)
- Auth Service (`services/auth-service`, port 8085)
  - JWT issuance/verification; JWKS endpoint; MFA hooks; integration keys.
  - Emits security activity events (e.g., `security.mfa.activity`).
  - Vault integration in entrypoint to load secrets.
- Product Service (`services/product-service`, port 8081)
  - CRUD for products; audit event emission; Prometheus metrics at `/internal/metrics`.
  - Emits `product.created`.
- Inventory Service (`services/inventory-service`, port 8087)
  - Stock, locations, and reservations (multi-location supported). Consumes `order.completed`, `order.voided`, `payment.completed`, `product.created`.
  - Emits `inventory.low_stock` and audit events.
- Order Service (`services/order-service`, port 8084)
  - Order lifecycle (including exchanges/returns and idempotency), settlement reporting, tax-rate overrides.
  - Consumes `payment.completed`; emits `order.completed`, `order.voided`.
- Payment Service (`services/payment-service`, port 8086)
  - Payment flows and auditing; typically fronted by the Integration Gateway.
- Integration Gateway (`services/integration-gateway`, port 8083)
  - API-key usage, request validation, rate limiting via Redis, webhook handlers.
  - Emits `payment.completed`; writes usage records; integrates with Vault in entrypoint.
- Customer Service (`services/customer-service`, port 8089)
  - PII encryption per-tenant using data-encryption keys (DEKs) protected by a master key.
  - GDPR delete/export flows; Prometheus metrics at `/internal/metrics`.
- Loyalty Service (`services/loyalty-service`, port 8088)
  - Consumes `order.completed`; emits `loyalty.events`.
- Analytics Service (`services/analytics-service`, port 8082)
  - Consumes `order.completed`/`inventory.low_stock`; exposes health and metrics endpoints.
- Supporting: `audit-consumer` (debug/validation), `common/*` crates for auth, security, audit, observability, money, crypto.

Data & Multi-tenancy
- Single Postgres instance (dev) with service-scoped tables; every business table includes `tenant_id` and tenant indexes (e.g., `products(tenant_id)`).
- Tenancy enforcement via shared guards validates `X-Tenant-ID` against JWT claims.
- Customer PII uses per-tenant DEKs stored in DB; encrypted with a master key (`MasterKey`).

Messaging (Kafka Topics)
- Orders: `order.completed`, `order.voided`.
- Payments: `payment.completed` (and `payment.failed` consumption in Order Service).
- Products: `product.created`.
- Inventory: `inventory.low_stock`, `inventory.reservation.expired` (audit).
- Audit/Security: `audit.events`, `security.mfa.activity`, `security.alerts.v1`.
- Loyalty: `loyalty.events`.

Infrastructure & Runtime
- Docker Compose (dev): Postgres (5432), Redis (6379), Zookeeper (2181), Kafka (9092), Vault (8200), plus all services on their listed ports.
- Terraform (AWS) under `infra/terraform/dev`.
- Secrets: Vault entrypoints used for Auth and Integration Gateway; other services use env vars in dev.

Observability
- Health: `/healthz` on most services.
- Metrics: `/metrics` or `/internal/metrics` depending on service.
- Grafana/Prometheus configs under `monitoring/`; dashboards for Integration Gateway; alerts samples included.

Security Overview
- Auth: JWT with role/capability checks (`common_security`) and tenant guard.
- Tenancy: Required `X-Tenant-ID` header; validated against JWT tenant claim.
- Data protection: Per-tenant encryption for Customer PII; audit logging across domain actions.
- Rate limiting: Redis-backed limiter in Integration Gateway.
- TLS: Expected at the edge (reverse proxy/ingress) in production; local dev uses HTTP in Compose.

Gaps and Alignment Notes (vs. prior PDF)
- Device authentication: Not yet implemented server-side; client maintains a device identifier for offline idempotency, but backend auth is user/JWT-based. Treat device auth as a future enhancement.
- WebSocket order status: POS client scaffolds `ws://�/ws/orders`, but no WS endpoint exists in services; current implementation polls for status.
- Vault adoption: Auth and Integration Gateway use Vault at startup; other services currently rely on env vars in dev. Expand Vault usage for parity.
- TLS in dev: PDF implies TLS end-to-end; Compose uses HTTP for convenience. Production should terminate TLS at ingress/reverse proxy.
- GraphQL: Not implemented; REST-only today.
- Metrics path inconsistency: Some services use `/metrics`, others `/internal/metrics`. Consider standardizing.

